---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import ImageText from '../../components/ImageText.astro';
import BookingCTA from '../../components/BookingCTA.astro';
---
<Layout
	title="Marathon Runners & Endurance Athletes"
	description="Specialist care for runners, cyclists, triathletes and endurance athletes at every level."
>
	<PageHero
		title="Marathon Runners & Endurance Athletes"
		breadcrumb="Marathon Runners & Endurance Athletes"
	/>

	<ImageText
		image="/sports-physio/hero-running.jpg"
		imageAlt="Endurance runner training"
	>
		<p>Endurance sport places cumulative demands on the body that create a unique set of vulnerabilities. At Balance, we work with runners, cyclists, triathletes and endurance athletes at every level, from first-timers to seasoned competitors, providing the specialist care that keeps you moving forward. We are currently training individuals to swim the channel, climb mountains, run marathons and cycle everything from London to Brighton to L'Étape du Tour.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText
		reverse
		altBg
		image="/antigravity.webp"
		imageAlt="Anti-gravity treadmill at Balance Physio"
	>
		<p>Preventing niggles from turning into overuse injuries are the defining challenge of endurance sport, and we understand that telling you to stop is not an option. Our anti-gravity treadmill allows you to maintain and improve your cardio-vascular fitness and running form while addressing the issues causing injured tissues, so your training never has to stop completely. Running analysis and bike fitting identify any biomechanical inefficiencies that cause injury over hundreds of miles, while podiatry, sports massage and hydrotherapy keep your body recovering effectively between sessions.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText
		image="/slider-bike.webp"
		imageAlt="Cyclist on a long ride"
	>
		<p>At Balance, we understand that your race represents months of commitment and effort. Our 25-strong team works together to keep you on the road, on the bike and in the water, building towards your goal with a body that is strong, balanced and ready to perform when it counts most.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<BookingCTA />
</Layout>
